  <Name>Murgh Ka Korma</Name>
  <Serves>4</Serves>
  <Procedure>
    <string>Heat small frying pan over high heat. Add poppy seeds, coconut and cashews. Dry roast until they turn golden. Transfer to a blender with enough water to just cover and blitz into a fine puree </string>
    <string>Heat the oil over high heat, add whole spices and fry for a minute or so before adding in the curry leaves and onions. Fry for 8-10 minutes until the onions are soft and golden</string>
    <string>Stir in the ginger-garlic paste then add the chicken. Cook over high heat for 4-5 minutes to seal. </string>
    <string>Mix in ground spices and after 1 minute add the tomatos. When tom have softened, pout in the puree from the blender. Rinse blender with about 100 mL of water and pour this in as well. Season with salt. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for about 25 minutes or so until the chicken is cooked through and tender</string>
    <string>Serve with rice</string>
  </Procedure>
  <Notes>
    <string>Serves 4</string>
  </Notes>
